components.content:
This section is intended to provide the case manager with space to identify circumstances and factors which could influence how supervision of the client is approached.

Please select which Specific Factors apply:

components.label: Indigenous considerations
components.tooltip: Does the client identify as indigenous (including Metis)? If so, note any available information regarding the client's nation and band affiliation. Is the client connected to cultural supports in the community?

components.label: Please specify in the field below
Mental health and/or cognitive functioning concerns
components.tooltip: This can include any suspected, self-identified, or confirmed  mental illness, brain injury, learning challenges, or other cognitive issues that could impact the client's functioning or require an adaptive approach to delivering meaningful interventions.

components.label: Please specify in the field below
Previous responses to supervision and motivation to engage in interventions
components.tooltip: Note the level of compliance and engagement during previous periods of supervision. How is the client's history of reporting? Have they completed any programs? What is their current level of motivation to engage in interventions?

components.label: Please specify in the field below
Barriers to communication
components.tooltip: Note the presence of any language or literacy barriers as well as any cognitive factors that could impact communication. If applicable, are you aware of any strategies to assist in communicating with the client

components.label: Please specify in the field below
Trauma informed approaches to supervision
components.tooltip: Are you aware of any past trauma that could be impacting the client’s responsivity? Are there strategies or adaptations that can be employed to minimise the client's trauma response?

components.label: Please specify in the field below
Gender based considerations for LGBTQ2+ clients
components.tooltip: Considerations include the client’s gender identity, preferred pronouns, name, etc. Note any adaptations to consider in meeting the client's program needs. Is client connected to any community supports/allies?

components.label: Please specify in the field below
Strength based considerations
components.tooltip: Outline strengths that can be engaged to maximise the potential for success. Examples can include resiliency, programming/treatment completed, learning style, strengths/hopes, etc. What are the client's goals? What motivates them?
